ONS API Get population data for England, Northern Ireland, Scotland, and Wales¶

In [12]:
def get_population(divider=1):
    areaCodes = {'E92000001': 'England', 'N92000002': 'Northern Ireland',
                 'S92000003': 'Scotland', 'W92000004': 'Wales'}
    populations = {}
    for areaCode, country in areaCodes.items():
        url = f'https://api.beta.ons.gov.uk/v1/datasets/mid-year-pop-est/editions/mid-2019-april-2020-geography/versions/2/observations?time=2019&geography={areaCode}&sex=all&age=total'
        r = requests.get(url)
        obs = json.loads(r.content)
        population = obs['observations'][0]['observation']
        populations[country] = int(population) / divider

    return populations

Per 100k population data¶

In [15]:
def calculate_per_k(data, interest_var, per_var):
    data.loc[england_filter, per_var] = data.loc[england_filter,
                                                 interest_var] / population_data['England']
    data.loc[wales_filter, per_var] = data.loc[wales_filter,
                                               interest_var] / population_data['Wales']
    data.loc[scotland_filter, per_var] = data.loc[scotland_filter,
                                                  interest_var] / population_data['Scotland']
    data.loc[ni_filter, per_var] = data.loc[ni_filter,
                                            interest_var] / population_data['Northern Ireland']

Growth Factors¶

In [26]:
def calculate_growth_factor(data):
    data_return = []
    data_p = data.iloc[:, 3]
    for i in range(len(data_p)):
        prev_day = data_p.iloc[i - 1]
        curr_day = data_p.iloc[i]
        gf = curr_day / prev_day
        dates = data.iloc[i, 0]
        dataRet = (dates, gf)
        data_return.append(dataRet)
    return data_return[1:]
